President Joe Biden has announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to attend the Bicentennial Celebrations in Monrovia, Liberia on February 14, 2022. This event commemorates the arrival of the first Free Black Americans to Providence Island in 1822, which led to the establishment of the City of Monrovia and the Republic of Liberia in 1847. The delegation includes the Honorable Dana Banks, Special Assistant to the President and Senior Director for Africa, as well as the United States Ambassador to Liberia, the Secretary of the Smithsonian Institution, and the Bishop of the Fifth Episcopal District of the Christian Methodist Episcopal Church.